SIMPLE: truncation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Truncation
<hw>Trun*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>truncatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of truncating,
lopping, or cutting off.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being truncated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>The replacement of an edge or
solid angle by a plane, especially when the plane is equally inclined to
the adjoining faces.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trunch</ent>⟦br⟧
